        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(#95186): docs: subagent_ended hook fields (incl. targetSessionKey identity) aren't documented",
        "body": "Closes #95186\r\n\r\n## What Problem This Solves\r\n\r\nThe plugin-hooks documentation (docs/plugins/hooks.md) listed the `subagent_ended` hook but did not describe what fields the event carries. Plugin authors building against the hooks API \\u2014 such as agent-connector, an SDK that normalizes hook events across agent CLIs \\u2014 had no way to know that `subagent_ended` uses `targetSessionKey` as its identity field instead of `agentId`. Because `subagent_spawned` documents its extra fields (resolvedModel/resolvedProvider) and inherits `agentId` from a base type, it was reasonable to assume `subagent_ended` also had `agentId`. It does not; accessing `event.agentId` in a `subagent_ended` handler silently returns `undefined`.\r\n\r\n## Why This Change Was Made\r\n\r\nAdded a documentation line for `subagent_ended` in the Subagents section of `docs/plugins/hooks.md`, matching the existing pattern used for `subagent_spawned`. The new line names every field on `PluginHookSubagentEndedEvent` \\u2014 `targetSessionKey` (identity), `targetKind`, `reason`, `outcome`, `error?`, `runId?`, `sendFarewell?`, `accountId?`, `endedAt?` \\u2014 and explicitly notes that, unlike `subagent_spawned`, this event does not include `agentId`.\r\n\r\nA test suite (`src/plugins/hook-types-subagent-ended.test.ts`, 23 tests) was added to verify the type definition matches the documented fields and to prevent future drift between docs and types.\r\n\r\n## User Impact\r\n\r\nPlugin authors can now look at the hooks documentation and correctly identify `targetSessionKey` as the identity field for `subagent_ended` events, avoiding the silent `undefined` trap when reaching for `event.agentId`. No runtime behavior changes \\u2014 this is a docs-only addition with supporting tests.\r\n\r\n## Evidence\r\n\r\n**Tests**: 23 passed, 0 failed (1 test file, 802ms total)\r\n\r\n```\r\n RUN  v4.1.8 /workspace/repos/solodmd_openclaw\r\n\r\n \\u2713 plugins ../../src/plugins/hook-types-subagent-ended.test.ts (23 tests) 131ms\r\n\r\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\r\n      Tests  23 passed (23)\r\n   Start at  03:02:15\r\n   Duration  802ms (transform 358ms, setup 383ms, import 14ms, tests 131ms, environment 0ms)\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Changes**:\r\n- `docs/plugins/hooks.md` \\u2014 added one line in the Subagents section documenting all `subagent_ended` fields\r\n- `src/plugins/hook-types-subagent-ended.test.ts` \\u2014 new test file verifying `PluginHookSubagentEndedEvent` type structure, field completeness against docs, and the key distinction from `PluginHookSubagentSpawnedEvent` (no `agentId`)\r\n\r\n\r\n---\r\n### 🤖 AutoFix Assessment\r\n**Category:** docs\r\n**Difficulty:** easy\r\n**Confidence:** 0.95\r\n**Assessment:** Clear docs-only fix: add subagent_ended event documentation to docs/plugins/hooks.md, naming targetSessionKey as identity field and noting no agentId. Source type identified in src/plugins/hook-types.ts.",
